<dl id="n40037d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40037d">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40037d"> 37(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> volubile &amp; / stagnant / infants ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In every school the lowest class (&ldquo;infants&rdquo;) is the largest, because very many never get beyond it. &ldquo;The lowest class in many schools,&rdquo; say the Commission, &ldquo;is characterized by the presence of what in the Punjab are called &lsquo;volatile and stagnant infants.&rsquo; They remain in the school for several years, but are not promoted. <small> Rev W.S. Hunt, <a name="WSHI1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WSHI1"><cite title="source">India's Outcastes: A New Era</cite></a> (1924) 80</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
